@NODE 4. "REQUIREMENTS"

                  AMIGA Computer AGA or ECS
                  
                  OS2.0 or higher

                  FAST RAM

                  Entire JIWA packet

                  AMIKANJI
                  

@ENDNODE

@NODE 5. "GETTING STARTED"

 The first time JIWA asks the resolution of the screen, the request is by
 the O.S.,all resolution are available and the program works as well on
 graphics boards.
 JIWA uses at the same time JIS16 for information on the screen and
 JIS24 for the text. With lower characters are active the Kana mode's
 while in upper character go in Katakana mode.
 All special characters of HIRAGANA and KATAKANA exist:
 sha,shu,shi,sho
 ja,ju,jo
 Kya,Kyu,Kyo
 Bya,Byu,Byo
 Hya,Hyu,Hyo
 Pya,Pyu,Pyo
 Rya,Ryu,Ryo
 For small a,i,u,e,o to put "x" to the vocals. ex.(xa)
 A,I,U,E,O to put "X" to the vocals. ex.(XA)


@ENDNODE

@NODE 6. "漢字  (KANJI INPUT)"

            KanJi are present:
            ※ KanJi input 
                   
 In KanJi input you can search the KanJi in "ON YOMI" mode and "KUN YOMI" mode 

     LIST of KANJI available:

     ※ ON yomi

             DAI, ICHI, KA, SOO, KOO, GYOO, SHO, REN, SHUU, GEN, GON, YOO, NYUU
             TEN, DEN, KEN, CHOO, CHOKU, ZEI, KAN, JI, YUU, FUKU, HON, SHU, BAI
             MOTSU, BUTSU, CHAKU, KOO, TOO, KYOO, CHI, MOKU, KOKU, EKI, HO, PO
             KIN, JUU, DEN, SHA, SUI, ZOKU, KAN, EI, KAKU, SAKU, NICHI, NI
             TATSU, RAI, GAN, KU RYOO, RI, KON, BAN, DAI, TAI, NIKU, BOKU, YA.

     ※ kun yomi

               atsu, nara, koto, ha, hai, mi, nani, nan, asa, ta, no
               tamago, mo, naka, moto, sake, ka, mono, kutsu, shita, kuda, tsu
               taka, higashi, miyako, shi, me, kuro, aru, chika, shibu, tani, ya 
               kuruma, mizu, mise, utsu, hi, tomo, tachi, dachi, kuru, kagami
               wasu, ima, ooki, suki, watakushi, watashi, sakana, hashi, ai, toki
               o, oso, yoru.


@ENDNODE


@NODE 7. "動詞の打ち方  Typing Verbs"

With the mouse select the verb that you want convert, together the conjugation, 
and press the GADGET "A/V".
The program search the verb in SHUUSHIKEI form and if the verb is finded
display it in a window, you can accept with the return key or to exit with 
ESC key.


                  @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}

                                @{"Image" system "HD1:Utilities/Multiview >NIL: Verbs"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE 8. "形容詞の打ち方 Adjectives"

With the mouse select the adjective that you want convert, and select the 
GADGET "A/V".
The program search the adjective and if the adjective is finded, display it 
in a window, you can accept with the return key or to exit with ESC key.
                  

                  @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}

@ENDNODE

