@NODE 9.1. "PROJECT"


         @{b}NEW:@{ub}        
         This option clears all text in memory and refresh it.

        
         @{b}SCREEN MODE:@{ub}        
         If you want to change the screen resolution with this option
         you can. The prefs are saved in PROGDIR and when JIWA
         restarts it reads the last saved prefs.


         @{b}COPYRIGHT:@{ub}
         Author Copyright.


         @{b}MEM FREE:@{ub}
         Shows all free memory available.


         @{b}HIDE:@{ub}
         This option hides JIWA in WB TOOLS MENU.
         To reactivate JIWA select the name of the program
         in the tools menu or with the combination of the 
         ctrl lalt j keys.

 
         @{b}CLOSE:@{ub}
         Close all document opened
         @{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}


         @{b}QUIT:@{ub}
         To exit the program with requester.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.2. "FILE"


         @{b}EXTRA OPEN:@{ub}
         Opens a extra file format :
         ShiftJIS e EUC code.

            
         @{b}INCLUDE:@{ub}
         To include another file in JIS or NJIS code.


         @{b}SAVE:@{ub}
         Saves a file previously opened.


         @{b}SAVE AS:@{ub}
         Save mode, with this option you can save in the following
         formats: JIS code, NJIS code, SJIS code, NEC code, EUC code.


         @{b}DELETE:@{ub}
         JIWA is able to delete every file you want.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.3. "PRINT"


         @{b}PRINT:@{ub}
         Is possible the choice of 3 different types of print.
         Print the file with the font that JIWA use.
         @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}


         @{b}IFF:@{ub}
         A IFF file will be generated and saved. You can use it
         together a wordprocessor program.
         @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.4. "EDIT"


         @{b}CUT:@{ub}
         Cut all selected characters.


         @{b}COPY:@{ub}
         Copy all selected lines.

 
         @{b}PASTE:@{ub}
         Paste a previously copied line.


         @{b}MOVE:@{ub}
         Move a line from a current position to where the cursor 
         is located. Select the line or block and move the cursor
         where you want.


         @{b}UNSELECT:@{ub}
         If you have selected a line to copy and you don't want to
         copy, this option deselect the choice.


         @{b}DELETE SELECTED:@{ub}
         Clear all selected characters.


         @{b}SAVE BLOCK:@{ub}
         Save a block of the selected line.


         @{b}INSERT LINE:@{ub}
         Insert a new line above the cursor.


         @{b}DELETE LINE:@{ub}
         Delete line where the cursor is positioned.
 

@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.5. "SEARCH"


           @{b}FIND:@{ub}
           A simple mode to find in a document the specified kana or ascii
           characters, default is kana. Max input is of 20 characters. 
           With esc you abort the search.

 
           @{b}NEXT:@{ub}
           To find the next character.


           @{b}PREVIOUS:@{ub}
           Go back in find mode.


           @{b}REPLACE:@{ub}
           This finds and replaces the characters in input, max input is
           of 20 characters, default is kana. With esc you abort the search.

           @{b}GOTO:
                    @{b}TOP:@{ub}
                    Go to the first line

                    @{b}BOTTOM:@{ub}
                    Go to the last line

                    @{b}PAGE UP:@{ub}
                    Go back of one page

                    @{b}PAGE DOWN:@{ub}
                    Next page

                    @{b}LINE NUMBER:@{ub}
                    Input to go to the specified line.      


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.6. "INPUT SYSTEM"
 

           @{b}KANA:@{ub}
           To enter kana mode.


           @{b}JASCII:@{ub}
           To enter ascii mode. This is not a standard ascii
           input, but it takes to the JIS font.


           @{b}KANJI:@{ub}
           See  漢字  (KANJI INPUT).


           @{b}JIS CODE:@{ub}
           With this system if you know the number in JIS of the
           KANJI, you can enter in JIS database and so to search
           the word. E.G.: 
           the number @{i}3333@{ui} put on the screen the backspace character:
           The code is only four character.


           @{b}JIS TABLE:@{ub}          @{" JIS TABLE CONTROL " Link 10.}
           It is quicker than the JIS system.  the screen will
           display the JIS Table, that you can explore with
           cursor keys:
        
           ↑ @{b}UP ARROW@{ub} go to first page of the table.
 
           ↓ @{b}DOWN ARROW@{ub} go to  last page of the table. 
        
           → @{b}RIGHT ARROW@{ub} next page.
    
           ← @{b}LEFT ARROW@{ub} previous page.  

           The @{b}ARROW@{ub} key together with @{b}SHIFT@{ub} key go forward
           or backward of two page for time.

           The @{b}ARROW@{ub} key together with @{b}CTRL@{ub}L key go forward
           or backward of three page for time.

           When you have recognized the @{b}KANJI@{ub} with the mouse click
           on it for the choice.

           @{b}FLUSH INPUT:@{ub}
           This option is anomalous if you have a problem in typing
           use this option.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.7. "FONTS"


         Only @{b}JIS16@{ub} and @{b}JIS24@{ub} are available with this
         packet, but on the @{b}MONASH FTP@{ub} you can find all fonts
         that JIWA uses.

                                    @{b}ASIYA24@{ub}
       
         This option is only for the screen.

         @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui} 


@ENDNODE

@NODE 9.8. "DICTIONARY"


           @{b}DICTIONARY:@{ub}
           It's possible to search for a particular kanji through kana
           or JASCII input, in the public dictionary of JIM BREEN, EDICT.
     
                              @{b}FUNCTIONS@{ub}

           Next KanJi:
                              Right Cursor

           Previous KanJi:
                              Left Cursor

           Accept KanJi:
                              Return key

           Exit:
                              ESC key

           @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}
 
   
           @{b}KANJI INFO:@{ub}
           Take informations on the selected KanJi
           Select a KanJi with the mouse and in the menu select KanJi Info 
           @{i}@{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}@{ui}


           @{b}THESAURUS:@{ub} 
           @{i}@{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}@{ui}


           @{b}CONVERT:@{ub}
           Convert kana in KanJi character.

           Follow this steps:

           1 - Select with the mouse the kana word that you want convert
           2 - In the menu select Convert or press the gadget in the window
           3 - Now the program searches the inserted yomi, when it
               finds it, the KanJi in the window will be displayed as the
               first KanJi.
               You can search the wished KanJi with the right cursor or
               left cursor, when you find it, press return.
               @{i}NOT AVAILABLE IN UNREGISTERED VERSION@{ui}


           @{b}BUSHU:@{ub}

           @{i}@{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}@{ui}

              
           @{b}KAKU:@{ub}

           @{i}@{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}@{ui}


@ENDNODE


@NODE 9.9. "TEXT"


           @{b}DATE:@{ub}
           Write the date system and display it.


           @{b}TABS:@{ub}
           This function reformat the text through numeric input.
 
        
@ENDNODE


@NODE 9.10. "MISC"


         @{b}NUMERIC KEYS:@{ub}
         ON/OFF for the numeric functions. Use this to obtain more 
         control on the document. (Home PgUp End PgDn PrtScr)
         Default is ON. 

         @{b}HELP LINE:@{ub}
         Call the JIWA guide for a fast reading.

 
         @{b}INFO DOCUMENT:@{ub}
         This item shows all characteristics of the loaded document.



@ENDNODE


@NODE 9.11. "DOCUMENTS"


           @{i}@{i}FUTURE AVAILABILITY@{ui}@{ui}


@ENDNODE

@NODE 10. "JIS TABLE CONTROL"


           @{b}FIRST PAGE:@{ub}
           Go to first page JIS

           
           @{b}LAST PAGE:@{ub}
           Go to last page JIS


           @{b}FORWARD PAGE:@{ub}
           Next page JIS


           @{b}BACKWARD PAGE:@{ub}
           Back page JIS


           @{b}GOTO PAGE:@{ub}
           Input to go to the specified page.


           @{b}RETURN TO MAIN:@{ub}
           Return to editor


@ENDNODE


